 The ability to calculate the average age of a group of individuals lies within the field of mathematics, specifically arithmetic. The average age of the Ninja Turtles can be determined by adding all their ages together and dividing the sum by the number of turtles.

Here's the mathematical equation:
```
\boxed{
\text{{Average Age}} = \frac{\text{{Total Age}}}{\text{{Number of Turtles}}}
}
```
In this case, there are 4 Ninja Turtles and their ages are 2 sets of 15 years old and 2 sets of 17 years old. So the total age is:
```
\boxed{
\text{{Total Age}} = (2 \times 15) + (2 \times 17) = 30 + 34 = 64
}
```
Now, divide the total age by the number of turtles:
```
\boxed{
\text{{Average Age}} = \frac{\text{{Total Age}}}{\text{{Number of Turtles}}} = \frac{64}{4} = 16
}
```
Therefore, the average age of the Ninja Turtles is 16 years old.

